and the Leray spectral sequence for j is of the form

304Equationhodge-theory-i-6.2hodge-theory-i-6.2.xml6.2hodge-theory-i-6       E_2^{pq}       = \bigoplus _{\#Q=q} H^p(D_Q,\mathbb {Q}_l)\otimes \mathbb {Z}_l(-q)       \Rightarrow  H^{p+q}(U,\mathbb {Q}_l).     \tag{6.2}     

By the Weil conjectures [W1949], H^p(D_Q,\mathbb {Q}_l) is pure of weight p, so that E_2^{pq} is pure of weight p+2q.
As a quotient of a sub-object of E_2^{pq}, E_r^{pq} is also pure of weight p+2q.
By , d_r=0 for r\geq 3, since the weights p+2q and p+2q-r+2 of E_r^{pq} and E_r^{p+q,q-r+1} (respectively) are different.
Thus E_3^{pq}=E_\infty ^{pq}.
